name: Tom Wolf
tweet: Thank you to everyone– all across PA– who canvassed, made calls, drove people to the polls and who voted to assure Pennsylvanians of the future we deserve.  https://t.co/OqLnLEFEQN

name: Tom Wolf
tweet: Four years ago I stood before you ready to build a Pennsylvania we could be proud of. I am proud of the good work we’ve already done together. But I know we still have much to do. That’s why I’m ready to get back to work. Pennsylvanians, thank you for your support.  https://t.co/rXsIFoWHQa

name: Tom Wolf
tweet: Today, you also voted for integrity in public service -- for an honest government worthy of the trust of the people it serves. Thank you for voting to resume the journey to a healthy democracy and a healthy commonwealth.

name: Tom Wolf
tweet: Today, you voted to protect women's rights, access to quality & affordable health care, a stronger economy, & for a fairer PA for everyone, regardless of:  The color of our skin. The religion we profess. The person we love. Or our gender.  Thank you for doing this.

name: Tom Wolf
tweet: All across America, citizens did what you did today. They voted to put our nation back on track. They voted for better lives. They voted to hold on to our democracy. Here in Pennsylvania, you did the same thing.  https://t.co/dKioM0BRrp

name: Tom Wolf
tweet: Poll are closed in Pennsylvania, but if you are in line, STAY IN LINE. If you got in line before 8:00 PM, you are entitled to vote. ↻ RT

name: Tom Wolf
tweet: Thank you to everyone who voted so far today. My family and I are so grateful for your support. Polls are still open until 8PM. Find time to get to the polls if you haven’t already! #WolfPack  https://t.co/0TkTEZ5bBS
